From 21cb0f318693fc6bbb83eb97d6a9579b3112d7cf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Aaradhana Sahu <quic_aarasahu@quicinc.com>
Date: Wed, 19 Feb 2025 11:43:47 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 116/141] wifi: ath12k: Add support for 512 MB profile

Add support for the 512 MB profile, as the driver currently supports
only the 1 GB profile. The 512 MB profile is useful in scenarios where
memory constraints are a concern.

Make the following modifications to enable the 512 MB profile:

-Decrease the sizes of the transmit/receive descriptors and monitor ring.
-Inform the firmware about the 512 MB profile via the QMI initialization
service.
-Reduce the number of virtual device (vdev) counts to 8.
-Reduce number of station per radio.

Tested-on: QCN9274 hw2.0 PCI WLAN.WBE.1.3.1-00173-QCAHKSWPL_SILICONZ-1

Co-developed-by: Tamizh Chelvam Raja <quic_tamizhr@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Tamizh Chelvam Raja <quic_tamizhr@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Aaradhana Sahu <quic_aarasahu@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Raj Kumar Bhagat <quic_rajkbhag@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Johnson <jeff.johnson@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/Kconfig | 32 +++++++++++++++++++++++++
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/dp.h    | 25 ++++++++++++-------
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/hw.h    | 26 +++++++++++++++-----
